author: TNN
description: In Delhi, a 24-year-old businessman from Bihar, Arun Mehto, was murdered due to an illicit affair. Police arrested a couple after discovering the wife's relationship with Mehto. The husband, upon learning of the affair, coerced his wife to lure Mehto to a secluded area where he fatally struck him with an iron rod, disposing of the body in Maidan Garhi.
title: Delhi man learns of wife's affair, conspires with her to kill lover

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: Google co-founder Sergey Brin has returned from retirement to actively contribute to the company's AI development, driven by the transformative potential of generative AI. Brin is deeply involved in training Google's Gemini models, aiming for artificial general intelligence. He considers AI more impactful than previous tech revolutions, focusing on expanding Google's computational capabilities to meet the surging demand.
title: Google founder Sergey Brin on going back to work: There's just never been a ...

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: During his Berlin visit, external affairs minister Jaishankar firmly condemned the Pahalgam terror attack, asserting India's zero-tolerance stance on terrorism and its resolve against nuclear blackmail. He emphasised that all issues with Pakistan would be handled bilaterally, excluding third-party involvement. Discussions with German leaders focused on strengthening the India-Germany partnership, with Germany expressing support for India's right to self-defense.
title: 'India will never give in to nuclear blackmail, will engage Pak bilaterally': Jaishankar

author: TOI NEWS DESK
title: News wrap: EAM says Pahalgam attack meant to create fear, Trump targets Harvard; & more

author: TOI CITY DESK
description: In Jharkhand's Latehar district, security forces neutralized two key leaders of the Jharkhand Jan Mukti Parishad, a splinter Maoist group, during an operation on Saturday. Pappu Lohara, carrying a Rs 10 lakh reward, and Prabhat Ganjhu, with a Rs 5 lakh bounty, were killed in the encounter.
title: Pappu Lohara, top Maoist leader, among 2 killed in Jharkhand encounter

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The US has informed the WTO that it sees no basis for India's proposal to suspend concessions in response to American tariffs on steel and aluminium. India had proposed retaliatory duties on 29 American products, claiming the US tariffs would affect $7.6 billion in imports.
title: 'Will not discuss … ': US tells WTO that India has no basis to impose duties

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Bryce James, son of LeBron and Savannah James, celebrated his graduation from Sierra Canyon School, marking a significant milestone before joining the University of Arizona's basketball team. Savannah shared heartfelt photos and videos from the convocation ceremony, expressing immense pride and excitement for Bryce's future endeavors. The family, including LeBron and siblings Bronny and Zhuri, joined in the celebration.
title: Savannah James shares glimpse of son Bryce James’ convocation

author: ANUJA JAISWAL
description: Delhi's health minister reported 23 Covid-19 cases detected by private labs, prompting an urgent investigation to determine if they involve residents or travelers. While symptoms are mild, the government is prepared and coordinating with hospitals.
title: 23 Covid cases in 10 days; no reason to panic: Delhi govt

author: TOI LIFESTYLE DESK
description: Brother's Day 2025 is the perfect occasion to celebrate the unique bond shared with brothers, those built-in best friends who have been partners-in-crime and unwavering supporters. The article provides a collection of heartfelt and humorous messages, quotes, and social media captions to express appreciation for the brother who has been a constant presence through life's adventures.
title: Happy brother's day 2025: Top 50 wishes, messages and quotes to share

author: FAZAL KHAN
description: Mohammed Shami is working on his fitness for the upcoming Test series in England. He acknowledges the need to increase his workload after the IPL. Shami feels his and Bumrah's presence is important for leading the bowling attack. He is not satisfied with his IPL performance.
title: I'm managing my workload as much as possible: Mohammed Shami

author: BASAVARAJ MARALIHALLI
description: Seven men, accused in a 2024 gang-rape case, were released on bail after 17 months and celebrated their return with a large vehicle procession, sparking public outrage. Videos showed them waving and their supporters cheering, leading to re-arrests for bail violations and an ongoing investigation. The incident, initially reported as moral policing, involved a 26-year-old woman who identified the accused.
title: Karnataka: 4 back in jail after rape suspects get heroes’ welcome following bail

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: India strongly criticized Pakistan at the UN Security Council for its hypocritical stance on civilian protection, citing Pakistan's support for terrorists and recent attacks on Indian civilians and religious sites. India highlighted Operation Sindoor, launched in response to a terror attack, and accused Pakistan of cross-border shelling that severely damaged border communities in Jammu and Kashmir.
title: 'No credentials to speak about protecting civilians': India rips into Pakistan at UN

author: TOI BUSINESS DESK
description: The Reserve Bank of India's record dividend payout to the government, nearly Rs 2.7 trillion, was primarily driven by substantial dollar sales and foreign exchange gains. The RBI actively intervened in the forex market, becoming a major seller of reserves. Increased earnings from rupee securities also contributed, although tempered by falling G-sec yields.
title: RBI's record Rs 2.7 tn dividend fueled by USD sell offs & forex gains: SBI

author: TOI WORLD DESK
description: President Trump criticized Harvard University, saying they "have to change its ways" after the DHS threatened to remove their ability to enroll foreign students. He questioned the university's academic standards, particularly a remedial math course. However, a federal judge blocked the Trump administration's action, with Harvard claiming it was retaliation and unconstitutional, potentially affecting over 7,000 visa holders.
title: After Harvard, will US stop other universities from enrolling foreign students? What Trump said

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: External Affairs Minister Jaishankar addressed the German Council, highlighting the recent terror attack in Jammu and Kashmir as part of a broader pattern of cross-border terrorism aimed at destabilizing the region. He emphasized India's right to self-defense and the growing international support for its counterterrorism efforts, noting Germany's recognition of India's position.
title: Pahalgam attack meant to create fear psychosis, sow religious discord: Jaishankar

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru squandered a golden opportunity to seal a top-two finish in the IPL 2025 standings, falling to a 42-run defeat against Sunrisers Hyderabad on Friday. Chasing a daunting 232-run target—powered by Ishan Kishan’s scintillating unbeaten 94 off 48 balls—RCB needed a precise and aggressive approach with the bat.
title: RCB's top-2 finish in IPL 2025 is still alive - but only if this happens

author: TANUJ LAKHINA
description: Shubman Gill is set to succeed Rohit Sharma as India's Test captain, despite mixed leadership numbers. Teammates and coaches praise his calm demeanor, game understanding, and communication skills. Gujarat Titans, led by Gill, currently top the IPL table, but their middle-order vulnerabilities were exposed in a recent loss, highlighting the team's reliance on its top order.
title: 'Shubman Gill is someone who reads the game and communicates well'

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Janhvi Kapoor captivated at Cannes with a sleek, all-black ensemble, a departure from her previous shimmery pink look. Styled by her cousin Rhea Kapoor, the outfit paid homage to Yves Saint Laurent, featuring a vintage saucer hat and velvet jacket. A custom-made silk chiffon skirt by Anamika Khanna and exquisite yellow diamonds by Chopard completed the iconic, Hollywood-esque appearance.
title: Velvet, yellow diamonds, and a saucer hat: Janhvi Kapoor’s at Cannes 2025

author: TOI NEWS DESK
description: Shashi Tharoor leads a parliamentary delegation to the US, aiming to share India's experiences with terrorism and explain its current strategies. The team, including MPs from various parties and former ambassador Taranjit Singh Sandhu, will also visit Guyana, Panama, Brazil, and Colombia. Their mission is to present a united front against terrorism and seek global partnerships for peace and security.
title: 'Will not be silenced by terrorism': Tharoor's strong message as he departs for US

author: TNN
title: Major vs Major: Adultery angle emerges, CCTV request denied; here’s what happened

author: TOI TECH DESK
description: President Trump threatened a 25% tariff on all smartphones sold in the US but manufactured elsewhere, impacting companies like Apple and Samsung. This move aims to push smartphone production to the United States, despite experts deeming it unrealistic and potentially raising iPhone costs significantly. Trump expressed his dissatisfaction with Apple's manufacturing in India, insisting on domestic production to avoid tariffs.
title: Not just Apple, Trump has bad news for all phone companies with his 'June' deadline

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Despite a 42-run defeat against Sunrisers Hyderabad (SRH), stand-in skipper Jitesh Sharma sees it as a valuable learning experience for Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB). He acknowledged the team's rustiness and lack of initial intensity, but believes the loss provides an opportunity to analyze and improve before the IPL 2025 playoffs.
title: 'It's good to lose': RCB skipper after defeat against SRH

title: When Indian TV news made social media look sane

author: TOI ENTERTAINMENT DESK
description: Paresh Rawal has officially stepped away from 'Hera Pheri 3', sparking widespread discussion about his unexpected departure. New reports indicate that the actor has returned his signing amount to the film’s producers and has officially concluded his involvement in the anticipated sequel.
title: Paresh Rawal returns Rs 11 lakh to Akshay Kumar's production house: Report

title: Drills, arms test planned over Andamans, airspace closed

title: How RBI earns profit, decides dividend: Explained

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Neeraj Chopra secured second place at the Janusz Kusocinski Memorial in Poland, battling tough weather conditions to achieve an 84.14m throw in his final attempt. Julian Weber of Germany outperformed Chopra with an 86.12m throw, while Anderson Peters of Grenada finished third. Chopra will now concentrate on upcoming competitions in Paris and Ostrava.
title: Neeraj Chopra finishes 2nd in Poland with final-round effort - Watch

title: RBI to transfer record Rs 2.7 lakh crore dividend to govt, surpassing budget estimates

author: TOI SPORTS DESK
description: Sunrisers Hyderabad defeated Royal Challengers Bengaluru by 42 runs, marking RCB's first away loss in IPL 2025. Ishan Kishan's explosive 94 propelled SRH to 231/6. Despite a strong start from Salt and Kohli, RCB's chase faltered, leading to a collapse and a final score of 189. Cummins and Malinga starred with the ball, securing a morale-boosting victory for SRH.
title: RCB suffer first away defeat of IPL 2025 season
